Commentary: On a length, coming back in with the angle, outside off. Carey shoulders arms to it.
Length again, outside off. Carey leaves it alone.
Anderson continues to bowl in the outside off channel. Carey lets it through to the keeper.
Steep bounce from Anderson, around off. Carey gets hit on the gloves as he looks to defend it.
Wicket-maiden over! Excellent stuff from James Anderson. Touch fuller, on off, pushed to mid off.
Short in length, around the 4th stump channel. Green blocks it towards cover.
BEATEN! Wood generating some extra pace here. This was on a length and way outside off. Green has a poke at it away from the body and he misses it completely.
On middle, on a length, tucked away to square leg for a single.
Short of a length, on middle. Carey keeps it out.
On a length, on off. Carey defends it towards point now.
Good leave! Carey covers his off stump and lets this length ball through to the keeper.
On middle, on a length, Green pushes it back to Anderson who shows his foot skills to collect it.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Length again, on off. Green with solid defense. England have been rock solid with their bowling. Not many freebies given and look so sharp here.
On middle. Green pushes it back to Anderson who gets low to grab it.
Short in length, around off, Green pushes it through covers for a single.
On a length and on middle. Carey gets on his toes and tucks it to mid-wicket.

Mark Wood showing his skills here! A length ball, on middle, it lands and shoots off the deck. Green looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves. The ball lobs and drops well in front of the man at point.
Short in length, outside off. Green blocks it off the back foot.
Pacy stuff from Wood! Hurls a short ball now, on middle. Green sits under it.
On middle. Green looks to block it on the leg side but gets a soft leading edge back on the deck.
Length ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Length and angling on the pads. Green flicks it in front of square leg for a brace.
Fuller in length, outside off. Alex Carey strides forward and blocks it towards cover.
Anderson pulls his length back here, on leg. Alex Carey, on his toes, defends it out.
Good-length, around the off pole. Carey taps it to point.
Tad fuller, outside off. Alex Carey leans and pushes it towards mid on.
Change of angle this time. James Anderson goes over the wicket, serves a length ball, on leg. Alex Carey blocks it on the leg side.
Good-length, outside off. Alex Carey defends it out. A maiden for James Anderson.

AUSTRALIA ARE EVENTUALLY INTO THE LEAD. Did not feel that we will use that word eventually, when they were 76/1. And Ben Stokes is frustrated and furious with his luck. He charges in and goes full around off and generates an outside edge straightaway, as Green looks to defend. But it dies down on its way towards gully and manages to get past the diving fielder at third slip. Haseeb Hameed chases it down from gully and the batsmen return for the second. Stokes is fired up here.
On a length, outside off. Cameron Green blocks it solidly.
Tad fuller, on middle. Green lunges and defends it out.
Shaping back in a tad bit. A length ball, on the pads. Cameron Green looks to block this but misses and the ball hit him on the pads and rolls towards point.
Shorter one this time. Cameron Green ducks under it and lets that go through.
A length ball, on off. Green defends it out. Oh wait. Stokes has overstepped that. It has been called a NO BALL by the third umpire.
Back of a length, outside off. Green taps it to covers.
Short in length,on off. Carey taps it to point and takes a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
On a length, on off. Defended out.
A full ball now, on off. Green pushes it to mid on.
Short of a length, on off. Green looks to defend but it goes off the slice to point, well short of the fielder.
Short in length, on off. Green blocks it out.
FOUR! Welcome boundary for Australia! A length ball, on the pads, Green tickles it fine to the fine leg fence.
On a length, wide of off. Alex Carey leaves it alone.
A full-length delivery, on the pads. Alex Carey flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Tad shorter, darting it on the pads. Alex Carey misses his flick as the ball nips back in a tad.
On a length, on the pads. Alex Carey tucks it away towards fine leg for two runs.
Very full, on middle. Alex Carey taps it to mid-wicket.
Puling his length back, darting it on the pads. Alex Carey pushes it towards fine leg. A single taken.
A short ball, on the body. Alex Carey takes his eyes off this pacey delivery and gets hit on the bicep.
Short again, on middle. Carey tucks it towards fine leg. A single taken.
Another bouncer, around middle. Cameron Green ducks under it.
Change of length this time, goes full, outside off. Cameron Green leans forward and blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Cameron Green jumps and taps it towards point.
On length, outside off. Cameron Green drives it towards cover.
Full and way outside off. Carey tries to drag it from outside off as he looks to sweep but misses.
Tosses it up, on middle. Alex Carey now attempts the reverse-sweep and hits it well but Mark Wood puts in a dive at point and stops it.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Flatter and on off. Carey nudges it to mid-wicket.
Carey reverse-sweeps this full ball through point and collects a couple of runs.

Two taken! This was full and outside off. Carey sweeps it well and towards fine leg and scampers across for a couple of runs. Carey puts in a dive as the fielder has a shy at the keeper's end. That will also be Tea on Day 2.
Ollie Robinson starts the session with a short ball, on middle. Green ducks under it.
On a length, on off. Green hangs back and blocks it out.
FOUR! Straight as an arrow! A full ball, on middle. Green shows the full face of the bat and punches it straight down the ground for a boundary.
A length ball, around off, this one nips back in. Green looks to defend but the ball goes through the gate and hits him high on the pads.
Tad fuller, on off, pushed through covers for a single.
Length and on middle, this is flicked to deep backward square leg for a single.
Short and on the pads. Carey flicks it with soft hands to leg slip who collects it on a bounce.
Tossed up, on middle, Carey sweeps it to square leg for a single.
That was just away from kissing the edge! Quicker, flatter and around off. Green waits and looks to dab it away but misses.
Flatter and on off. Green defends it off the front foot.

OUT! Green has been adjudged LBW! But he has taken this upstairs. This looks dead close. Nothing on the Hot Spot. Time for RTS. Nothing. Ball away from the bat. Now then... now then.... big moment for Leach... UMPIRE'S CALL ON WICKETS! Australia hold on to a review but lose Green. Big, big wicket for Leach. He came in from around the wicket and slid this with the arm, around middle and leg. Green went back to flick but missed and was hit on the pads. The English camp immediately went up in appeal and umpire Paul Reiffel, after thinking for a while, raised his finger. Hawk Eye showed the ball to be sliding down the leg side, but on its way, just clipping the leg stump! Umpire's call stays to raise boos from the crowd. Australia 7 down. Just 22 ahead. Just the second wicket for Leach in the series. Might be the one which keeps the Ashes alive.
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

Commentary: Tosses it up, full and on middle. Cummins leans and pushes it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on middle. Carey is squared up as he looks to defend. Gets an outside edge wide of the diving third slip fielder and towards third man. Two taken.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling from Ollie Robinson! On a length, outside off. Carey looks to push but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
On middle, on a length, tucked away to mid-wicket.
Touch fuller, angling around off. Carey puts his front foot out and punches it wide of mid off for a couple of runs.
Short in length, outside off. Left alone.
Length and on off. Carey defends with his bat and pad together.
Full and slanting on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Beautifully bowled! Tosses it up, gives some flight to it and lands it on middle. Pat Cummins tries to defend but gets an outside edge past first slip for a couple of runs.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Slightly short and outside off. Cummins hits it to point for a single.
A  loopy delivery, on off. Carey defends it out.
Very full and on off. Carey reverse-sweeps it through point for a single.

Full, on the pads, Alex Carey leans and flicks it past mid-wicket, to his right. It is a long boundary and the batsmen have enough time to come back for the third. And they do. But should they have? Seems like Carey is trusting Cummins to hang on here. England will not mind Patrick on strike.
Fuller in length, around middle. Pat Cummins looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards fine leg. A single taken.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Forget Patrick, England have got Alex! It is Mr. 'Make-It-Happen', Ben Stokes. The last of the recognized batter departs. Australia just ahead by 34. Full, outside off, Carey, who is in one-day mode, reaches out to drive. But with an upright body and the knee of the back leg not quite getting down, the weight of the body could not quite get transferred onto the feet. By the time that could happen, the ball is already through and the outside edge is taken. Simple catch for Carey's counterpart.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Mitchell Starc leaves it alone.
Goes full on this occasion, around off. Mitchell Starc pushes it to mid on.

Stokes nearly had two! A good length, outside off. Mitchell Starc strides forward and looks to drive this. But he is too early into his shot, and manages to get an outside edge towards gully. The ball flies and falls just short of Haseeb Hameed at gully.
Tossed up, on off. Starc prods to defend.
Short ball, on the pads. Starc hangs on the back foot and tucks it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! The skipper goes up and over! This was full and on off. Pat Cummins lifts it over mid off and wide of long on for a boundary.
Flatter and on off, pushed to covers.
Full and on middle. Pat Cummins whips it down to long on for a single.
Tossing it up, around off. Mitchell Starc lunges and blocks it out.
Swing and a miss! Mark Wood serves a length ball, outside off. Pat Cummins swings his bat and gets beaten due to extra pace.
On a length, around off. Pat Cummins, on back foot, pushes it towards cover. A single taken.
Mark Wood goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander, serves a shortish delivery, around middle. Mitchell Starc blocks it out solidly.
Short of a length, around off. Mitchell Starc jumps and defends this one.
Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc hangs back and looks to chop this away, but fails to get any bat on it.
Shortish delivery again, outside off. Mitchell Starc taps it to cover and scampers through to the other end.
Ben Stokes delivers a short ball, on middle. Mitchell Starc waits back and pulls it away towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length, around middle. Pat Cummins pushes it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Pat Cummins blocks it on the leg side.
Nicely cut away! A length ball, outside off. Pat Cummins waits back, and chops it through covers. Two runs taken.
On a length again, on the pads this time. Pat Cummins flicks it away to the right of mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball, over middle. Mitchell Starc doesn't get hold of his pull shot but manages to get a single towards square leg.
On a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc, on back foot, goes for the push but gets beaten as the ball zips past through the outside edge.
Drops it short again, on the body. Mitchell Starc gets an inside edge onto the body. The ball rolls towards short fine leg. A single taken.
Back of a length, outside off. Pat Cummins dabs it to backward point.
Angling it onto the pads, a length delivery. Pat Cummins nudges it towards mid-wicket and scampers through to the other end. Australia now leads by 50 runs.
Short of a length, down the leg this time. Mitchell Starc misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Shortish in length again, outside off. Mitchell Starc makes room and drops it towards cover.
Anderson starts from around the wicket, full ball and on middle. Starc whips it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Cummins punches it through point for a single.
A length ball, on off. Starc defends it back on the deck.
Length and on middle. Starc clips it to square leg for a single.
Length ball, on middle. Cummins defends it out.
Anderson continues to bowl straight and on the stumps. Cummins flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Straight down the ground! A full ball, on middle. Cummins punches it past the bowler and down the ground for a boundary.
A length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Around off, this is pushed to point.

DROPPED! James Anderson almost pulls off a blinder! Honestly, it is harsh to call that a drop but if there is someone who can take stingers in this team, it is Jimmy. He has taken plenty of these in the past and would have hoped that this one stuck too. Full, around middle, Pat Cummins backed away and swung hard. The ball went off the inner half of the bat slightly wide of mid on. Anderson there, dived full stretch to his right and almost pulled it off, but unfortunately for him, the ball did not stick. A single taken.
Full ball, outside off. Starc drives it nicely but straight to covers.
A length ball, outside off. Starc leaves it alone to the keeper.
BEATEN! A length ball, outside off. Pat Cummins drives it away from the body and misses it completely. Good bounce and carry. England will hope that the tail doesn't wag for a long time.
Full ball, on off, pushed to covers.
On a length, on off, Cummins chops it to point. He wanted a single but was sent back.
A length ball, outside off. Cummins works it to point.
Another swing and a miss! A full ball, outside off. Cummins looks for a big booming drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, on off. Starc punches it to covers.

DROPPED! Toughie, toughie for Robinson and dear me, what do we see next? ROBINSON IS CATCHING HIS HAMSTRING! No, England do not need this. Coming to the ball, it was full and straight. Mitchell Starc did not need any second invitation and went straight back. However, the bat came before the ball could arrive. The ball took the inner half of the bat and went towards Robinson. But the bowler seemed to react a bit too soon. He felt the ball would come quicker but it came on slower than his anticipation. As a result, he was surprised and could not quite take it in the first attempt. Tried to do it in the second but then, the spikes on his shoes gave away and he slipped, with the ball slipping out too. And that, affected his hamstring too.
A length ball, outside off. Starc shoulders arms to it.
Valuable runs! A length ball, on off. Starc looks to go straight but it takes the splice and goes through point for a couple.
On middle. Starc again gets lucky as he hits it off the slice through covers and another couple of runs are added to Australia's lead.

FOUR! TONK! 250 UP FOR AUSTRALIA! The lead has now swelled to 65, 34 of which, have come in this 9th-wicket stand! A short ball, around off, angling away, Mitchell Starc gets on top of the bounce and pulls it audaciously over mid-wicket!
Touch fuller, on off, pushed to mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT! The quickfire stand is broken. 34 in 53 balls. A length ball, outside off, Pat Cummins backs away and swings like there is no tomorrow. But there is lack of pace on the ball, which means the shot is played in July, while the ball arrives in the month of December. A top edge is induced and Haseeb Hameed takes the simplest of catches at backward point. Decent knock by the skipper. Australia lead by 68.
Howout: c Haseeb Hameed b James Anderson

Commentary: Short of a length, on middle. Starc stands tall and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Scott Boland leaves it alone to the keeper.
On a length, on off. Boland blocks it towards cover. Can he survive this over?
Yes, he does! This was on a length and way outside off. Boland offers no shot to it.
Tad slower this time, outside off. Mitchell Starc shoulders arms to it.
Short of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc looks to play that but gets beaten by the lack of pace.
Back of a length, around the off pole. Mitchell Starc guides it towards third man and rotates the strike.

LEG BYE! An LBW shout but the umpire signals a leg bye. A full delivery, drifting onto the pads. Scott Boland misses his flick and gets rapped on the pads. A shout for LBW but umpire thinks otherwise. The batters steal a leg bye in return.
Short delivery, Starc swivels across and pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
On length, outside off. Scott Boland leaves that alone.
Full in length, around off. Mitchell Starc pushes it down towards long on for a single.
Beaten! A peach of a delivery, A full ball, just outside off. Scott Boland goes for the drive but gets beaten as the ball nips away a tad bit.

The MCG roars! Oh... how much do they love their lads...Full, outside off, Scott Boland lunges, opens the face of his bat and guides it behind point, for his first runs in Test cricket! The crowd almost gives a standing ovation! Two runs taken.
Shortish delivery, on the thigh pad. Scott Boland flicks it away towards square leg for a single.
On a good-length, around off. Mitchell Starc presses forward and looks to defend that gets a slight inside edge towards mid-wicket.
Fuller, outside off. Mitchell Starc drives it straight to the fielder at cover.
Mark Wood serves a full-length delivery, on the pads. Scott Boland uses his wrists and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket. Three runs taken.
Adding some handy runs here these two! Short of a length, outside off. Mitchell Starc chops it through backward point for two runs.
Fuller this time, outside off. Mitchell Starc drives and gets an outside edge towards deep point for a single.
Short in length, outside off. Scott Boland offers no shot on that.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! And England finally bowl out Australia. The lead stops at 82. A length ball, outside off, Scott Boland stays inside the line and looks to slice it through the off side. But the extra pace defeats him and he is late into the shot. The outside edge is taken and Zak Crawley takes a nice catch at second slip. AUSTRALIA BOWLED OUT FOR 267!
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Mark Wood

Commentary: Starc starts with a fullish delivery, slanting way outside off. Haseeb Hameed lets it through to the keeper.
Starc drags his length ball, and keeps the outside off line. Haseeb Hameed watches it all the way through to the keeper.
This was much better. On a length, just around the 4th stump channel. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it.
Full ball, angling outside off. Haseeb Hameed with yet another leave. Mitchell Starc is yet to target the stumps!
England and Haseeb Hameed are underway! Short of a length, on the hips. Haseeb Hameed flicks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Full ball, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.

Leg bye! In the air and drops safe! It came off the arm though! Fiery start from Pat Cummins. Short of a length, on middle. Haseeb Hameed ducks but keeps his bat out. The ball hits him on the arms and lobs over the slip cordon. A leg bye given.
Full ball, outside off. Defended out.
BEATEN! Pat Cummins with his probing lines! What delivery! This was on a length and outside off. Zak Crawley looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, on off, it lands and jags back in. Zak Crawley is beaten on the inside edge and gets hit high on the pads.
This one swings back in very late. Full ball, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Brilliant over from Pat Cummins!  A length ball, on middle. Zak Crawley solidly defends it.
JAFFA! Two experienced guys going against two inexperienced players. Serves a short ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed stands tall and the ball whizzes past the blade.
Length ball, outside off. Hameed leaves it alone.
Full ball, slanting outside off. Hameed lets it through to the keeper.
On a length, on middle. Hameed gets inside the line and blocks it out. Good defense from Hameed.
Short in length, slanting outside off. Hameed shoulders arms to it.
Maiden over! A length ball, outside off. Hameed has a poke to this wayward delivery and misses it completely. What a start from Australia!

An appeal for LBW but not given. Might be drifting down. Yes, and missing the stumps as well. This was on a length and angling on middle and leg. Zak Crawley misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Length ball, outside off, steep bounce there and Zak Crawley leaves it alone.

EDGED, MISSED, FOUR! This is not done by Carey. That is the second time in two matches he has been reluctant to go for a catch. Full, around middle, swinging away, Zak Crawley has a tentative poke at it. Gets a thick outside edge, which flies right between the keeper and first slip. Now, when this happens, it has to be the keeper's catch. Alex Carey makes an initial movement to his right but does not go for it in the end. David Warner at first slip is looking at Carey and naturally, seeing the keeper's initial movement, he stays still. The ball escapes through the gap, to the third man fence. The last time Carey did this mistake, Jos Buttler almost made them pay in Adelaide. Is it going to be more of the same with Crawley?

WOW! What a delivery! The ball is swinging sharply here! A length ball, on off, this one nips back in sharply. Zak Crawley is beaten on his defense and the ball whizzes past the inside edge and the ball bounces over the stumps. Good carry for Alex Carey as well.
A length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Touch fuller, on middle. Zak Crawley leans and looks to flick but gets an inside edge to square leg for a single.

An appeal for caught behind but Starc was not interested that! Short of a length, on off. Zak Crawley without any foot movement looks to defend but misses. The ball takes the thigh pad on its way to the keeper. A muted appeal follows mostly from the slip cordon.
Length and on off, Defended out.
A length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Starc strikes! Crawley fails to make use of the reprieve given to him by Carey. Excellent line and length by Mitchell Starc. He was struggling in his first over but since then, has found some rhythm. And now, that rhythm has got him a wicket. Nothing much that Crawley could really do here. He is constantly waiting for the ball to come in but this one moves away a bit. Takes the outside edge and Carey does the rest. Actually, he does not go up but Warner at first slip is charging at the umpire. Starc celebrates too. But Crawley is not going anywhere as the umpire has not raised his finger. Well, they appeal now and up goes the finger! Crawley does not bother reviewing.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Is it two in two? Malan has taken a review. What does Hawk Eye suggest? Hit high on the knee roll. UMPIRE'S CALL AND STARC IS ON A HAT-TRICK! One of the worst first balls to get, if you are a batsman and that too, against Starc. A length ball, outside off, Malan stays back and looks to work it on the leg side but his feet are not quite warmed up to the occasion. The ball jags back in, beats the bat and hits the pad. The umpire raises his finger on the appeal and Malan reviews but it is a golden duck for Dawid.
Howout: lbw b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: ALMOST A HAT-TRICK! Saved by a hair's breadth. Phew! What an over from Mitch. How did he survive that? Full, around off, Joe Root is forced to play at that but the ball nips away off the seam and almost takes the outside edge. Root survives as the MCG roars. Cannot blame them. We all thought that took the edge. But Starc just smiles and walks off. When was the last time we actually saw Starc smile in a match? It has been a torrid year for the speedster. Good to see him in high spirits.

NOT OUT! A huge appeal for LBW, but turned down by the umpire! The Aussies are on fire here! Pat Cummins bowls in fuller length, nipping it back into Haseeb Hameed. Haseeb Hameed looks to block that but gets beaten and the ball hits him high on the pads. The replay confirms that would have missed the wickets.
Full in length, around off. Haseeb Hameed blocks it watchfully.
Shaping it back in, On a fuller length. Haseeb Hameed gets an inside edge towards square leg. A single taken.
Beaten! A shorter delivery, outside off. Joe Root gets beaten as the ball zips through the outside edge.
FOUR! Something to smile about for England! Pat Cummins overcooks this one, outside off. Joe Root punches it past mid off for a four!
Tad shorter, outside off. Joe Root leaves that alone.
JAFFA! These two are keeping the batters on their toes. A short ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed stands tall and keeps the bat away from the line of the ball.
Fuller ball, outside off. Hameed leaves it alone.
A length ball, on middle. Hameed flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Root shoulders arms to it.

EDGED, FOUR! Dear me, through the slip cordon, that too, a packed one! Full, outside off, a touch wide, Joe Root flays hard at that, as he looks to drive. But the pace from Starc induces an outside edge and it flies. But between third slip and gully, to the third man fence!
Short of a length, on middle. Root hops and blocks it back on the deck.

A huge appeal for LBW but not given. Australia opt not to take the review. That one came sharply. On a length, around off and comes back in sharply. Haseeb Hameed leaves but this one shapes in and hits him on the pads. That looked really close.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
A short ball, on middle. Hameed sits under it.
On a length and on off. Hameed defends it on the off side.
Short of a length, just around off. Hameed does really well as he stays away from the line of the ball.
A full ball, outside off. Hameed toe-ends it as he pushes it back to the bowler.
Targets the stumps, Root defends it solidly.

A length ball, outside off. Root tries to defend with soft hands but it takes the outside edge and the ball falls just short of the keeper, Alex Carey who dives to his right and palms it away to third man. A single.
Length and outside off. Left alone.

FOUR! First boundary from Hameed's blade! Starc pitches it up and bowls it around off. Hameed pushes it nicely past mid off. The fielder gives a chase but to no avail as the ball races away to the fence.
Short ball, outside off. Hameed leaves it alone.
Eventful over from Starc. This was on a length, outside off. Hameed looks to push but gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls to the slip cordon.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Short of a length, angling on middle. Root is squared up as he looks to defend. Gets hit high on the pads.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Outside off. Root with an easy leave.
On a length, on off. Root hops and taps it to point.
A full ball, on off. Root toe-ends his drive to mid on.
A length ball, outside off. Hameed leaves it alone.
Boland serves a length ball, outside off. Hameed offers no shot there.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Boland strikes immediately on being given the cherry in the second innings! He is pumped up and the MCG roars along with him. Almost a replica of Hameed's dismissal in the first innings of this Test and the second innings of the previous Test. On a length, in the avenue of apprehension, around off, Haseeb Hameed is not sure whether to play or let it go. He puts bat on ball pretty late but a tinge of late away movement takes the outside edge. Simple catch for Alex Carey.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Scott Boland

Commentary: Almost played it on! Scott Boland is fired up. A length ball, on off. Jack Leach defends it under his eyes. The ball bounces just over the stumps and missed by inches. Not just Boland but Australia and the whole MCG is pumped up here. England nowhere to be seen.

OUT! BOWLED! Left alone and gone! Well, Leach did not want to play at that and as Ian Chappell always says - 'Mate, you have got a bat, use it!' On a length, outside off, Jack Leach shoulders arms, probably trusting the bounce on this deck and expecting it to go over. But to his horror, the ball nips back in and hits the top of middle stump! It can be put down to misjudgement of length but really difficult to judge at this time of the day. Cannot blame Leach much there. England are 4 down in next to no time!
Howout: b Scott Boland

Commentary: What an over by Scott Boland! A length ball, angling on middle. Ben Stokes shuffles in his crease and flicks it to deep square leg for a single. He takes his position after the over at deep square leg and there is applause from behind for him.
A length ball, on middle. Ben Stokes wrists it to deep square leg for a single.
BEATEN! This is outstanding bowling from Cummins! A length ball, outside off. Joe Root has a poke away from the body but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR LEG BYES! Flies away from the keeper! A full ball, slanting way down the leg side. Root misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls away from the diving keeper and races away to the fine leg fence.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, on off. Root hits it to point. Last ball of the day coming up. Can Root hold onto it?
Root finishes the day with peace! A full ball, very full, on middle. Root punches it down the ground before the fielder cuts it off. Three taken. That will be STUMPS on Day 2.
Starc serves it on a length, on off. Root pushes it to cover.
BEATEN! It doesn't take long for Starc to correct his line. Short of a length, outside off. Root looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short in length, on off. Root punches it through point for a couple.
This was full and on middle. Root eases it to mid on.
FOUR! Root with positive intent! A full ball, on off. Root drives it nicely and wide of mid off for a boundary.
Another good looking drive from Root! A full ball, angling on off, driven to covers.
Serves a full ball, on off. Stokes defends it off the front foot.
On a length, on the pads. Stokes rocks back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads. Stokes shuffles across and flicks it to square leg for a single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Joe Root leans and blocks it out.
On a length, outside off. Joe Root, on back foot, pushes it towards gully.
Shortish delivery, outside off. Joe Root leaves that alone.
A length ball, on middle. Stokes defends it solidly. The wicket looks flat and it is nice to bat on.
Short of a length, outside off. Stokes leaves it alone.
Starc continues to serve it on a length, on middle. Stokes nudges it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Good signs from England early on! A full ball, on middle. Stokes punches it through mid on and the ball races away to the fence.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket. The fielder there dives and stops it.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
A length ball, on off. Root prods and defends it under his eyes.
Length ball, around the 5th stump channel. Left alone. The ball is rolling straight, no signs of movement till now.
On a length, on off. Root defends it on the off side.
Finally some inward movement. A length ball, on off. Root defends it more off the inner half of his blade back on the deck.
A short ball, on off. Root sways away from the line of the ball.
Length ball, outside off. Root blocks it to covers.
Starc continues to target the stumps. Stokes is solid in his defense.
Length and on middle. Defended out.
FOUR! This is good and positive cricket from England! A full ball, outside off. Stokes drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Now looks to drag it on the off side but gets an inside edge to mid-wicket.

OUT! TIMBER! Superb stuff from Mitchell Starc! Just when you thought that England will fight, Starc comes with his brilliance. This was a full-length delivery, some inward movement and it is enough for the ball to roll through the gap as Stokes looks to defend away from the body. The ball rattles the middle stump and Australia get the big wicket. England trail by 36 runs.
Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: A length ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow gets inside the line of the ball and defends it.
Quick single! A length ball, on off. Root taps it on the top, towards cover and takes a quick single.
Jonny Bairstow is off the mark! A length ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow tucks it with soft hands to deep square leg for a brace.
EDGED AND JUST SHORT! A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow lunges and tries to defend but the ball shapes slightly away and takes the outside edge. Green carries it on a bounce to gully.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, angling on off. Jonny Bairstow knocks it to point.
Now a short ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow lets it through to the keeper.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, on middle. Root blocks it on the leg side.
A length ball, way outside off. Root with an easy leave.
A length delivery, outside off. Joe Root looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Anything that is loose and Root pouches on it. Beautiful shot! Pitches it up, on off. Root drives it straight down the ground for a boundary. Holds the pose for a while as well.
Outside off. Left alone.
Ohh, What was that? A length ball, on off, it wasn't that short but the ball climbs off the deck. Jonny Bairstow looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the shoulder.
On a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow tucks it to square leg and takes a quick single. There is a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Root was well in.

Root gets hit on the box and he is in some pain here. Deja vu for Root after getting hit at the same area in Adelaide as well. A length ball, on middle. Joe Root looks to defend but gets hit near the groin area.
A length ball, outside off. Root stands tall and punches it to point.
A length ball, slanting outside off. Root shoulders arms to it.
This one comes back in with the angle, on off. Root solidly defends it on the surface. Quality stuff from Pat Cummins, so accurate with his lines and lengths.
Touch fuller, outside off. Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms to it.
Starc pulls his length back here, around leg. Jonny Bairstow blocks it towards short leg.
On a length, around middle. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards gully with the outer half of his bat.
Mitchell Starc changes his angle now, goes around the wicket, serves a length ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow jumps and blocks it from the toe-end of his bat.
Tad shorter, outside off. Jonny Bairstow guides it to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to the man at point. A maiden over for Mitchell Starc.
Cameron Green begins with a length delivery, on middle, getting the ball to nip back in a tad. Joe Root blocks it out.
Good-length delivery again, on middle. Joe Root defends this one.
A shorter one this time, on the body. Joe Root pulls it towards fine leg. A single taken.

Extra bounce! Cameron Green serves a back of a length, on the body. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend that but misses as the ball bounces off the surface and hit the top of the bat and lands just wide of gully. A single taken.
Fuller this time, outside off. Joe Root pushes it towards mid on.
Length, outside off. Joe Root blocks it towards point.

DROPPED! That was quick and it needed reflexes from Cameron Green! Short of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to cut off the back foot but gets a thick outside edge to gully where Cameron Green dives to his left and fumbles it. Good start from Scott Boland.
Short of a length, outside off. Joe Root, on back foot, blocks it out.
Nicely done! Scott Boland serves a back of a length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back, jumps a tad and punches it solidly through the covers for three runs.
On a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Jonny Bairstow reviews it straightaway. No bat there clearly, confirmed by UltraEdge as well. Ball Tracker is umpire's call and the same on wickets hitting. Jonny Bairstow retains the review but he does not retain himself here. Scott Boland can do no wrong here. He is loving life at the moment. A length ball, around off, this one nips away. Jonny Bairstow is early as he looks to flick and gets hit on the back pad. Height was the only issue. An appeal for LBW and the umpire takes his time before raising his finger. Joe Root shakes his head as he watches wickets tumbling on the other end.
Howout: lbw b Scott Boland

Commentary: JAFFA! What a peach of a delivery! Scott Boland delivers a back of a length, outside off. Jos Buttler looks to defend but gets beaten as the ball zips past the outside edge.
A length delivery, angling it onto the pads. Joe Root jabs it towards gully.
Shorter, around off. Joe Root pushes it towards mid-wicket and scampers through to other end.
Back of a length, outside off. Jos Buttler leaves that alone.
On a length, on middle. Jos Buttler blocks it out.
Good-length, outside off. Jos Buttler pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller this time, on middle. Jos Buttler lunges and blocks it out solidly.
Short of a length, outside off, punched to point.
This is full and outside off. Root shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, on off. Root defends it off the front foot on the off side.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE!  It is the captain and Australia have one hand on the series. Scott Boland with a beautiful delivery. Surely that was the wicket Australia were looking for and there are all smiles in the camp now. Boland hurls and serves a full-length delivery, angling outside off. Joe Root looks to drive but away from the body. It takes the outside edge and goes to David Warner at first slip holds onto it. It is all in hands of the Jos Buttler now to at least keep the hopes alive.
Howout: c David Warner b Scott Boland

Commentary: Shorter delivery, outside off. Mark Wood gets beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend.
Beaten again! A fuller length this time, outside off. Mark Wood lunges and looks to block that but gets beaten once again.
Cameron Green drops it short, on middle and leg. Jos Buttler hops and blocks it out.
Back of a length again, around middle and leg. Jos Buttler hangs back and defends it out.
Too short on this occasion, around middle. Jos Buttler ducks under it.
A length delivery, outside off. Jos Buttler plays this with soft hand and gets an outside edge towards gully.
FOUR! Glorious drive! Cameron Green misses his length, serves a low full toss ball, outside off. Jos Buttler lunges and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Short in length, outside off. Jos Buttler pushes it towards covers.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Extraordinary scenes here at the MCG! Baggy Green and then a five-fer. Take a bow Scott Boland! Just what dreams are made of. This was on a length and on off. Mark Wood stays back and chips it back to the bowler. Scott Boland gets his hand down in time and everything is happening as he likes right now The ball sticks to his hands nicely. All the players appreciate and gather around him. Boland waves the ball to the dugout as he celebrates his wicket.
Howout: c & b Scott Boland

Commentary: Beaten! Another ripper by Scott Boland! A length delivery, around the fourth stump line. Ollie Robinson, on back foot, looks to defend but gets beaten as the ball whizzes past the outside edge. An appeal for caught behind. But the umpire says no.

OUT! TAKEN! We are running out of words for Scott Boland! What has he had for breakfast because England are not liking it at all! Unbelievable scenes here at MCG! A length ball, outside off, this one nips slightly away. Ollie Robinson has a poke at it and gets a thick outside edge to third slip where Marnus Labuschagne takes a good low catch. 6 wickets for just 5 runs. Extraordinary figures by Scott Boland.
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Scott Boland

Commentary: Anti-climax! A length ball, on middle. James Anderson tucks it to deep square leg for a brace. The crowd is shouting Boalnd! Boland! Boalnd! They are loving the home boy right now.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Length and on off. James Anderson defends it out.
On a length, outside off. Jos Buttler looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A short ball, down the leg side. Jos Buttler looks to pull but misses.
Fuller delivery, outside off. Jos Buttler pushes it to covers and scampers through to the other end, which brings James Anderson on strike. Australia will be happy with that.

OUT! TIMBER! Dominance, just dominance from Australia! Green takes his first wicket and runs with joy. Incredible scenes here at MCG! A cracker of delivery to seal the series though. This was on a length and around off, it lands and shapes in sharply. James Anderson is squared up as he looks to defend and the ball hits the off stump.
Howout: b Cameron Green
